snippet: Lt. Col. Jeffrey Krusinski, 42, who once led the branch’s sexual assault response team, was acquitted on charges that he had grabbed a woman outside a Virginia bar.
abstract: Seven-member jury acquits Lt Col Jeffrey Krusinski, Air Force officer who once led the branch's sexual assault response team, on charges that he groped a woman outside a Virginia bar; Krusinski's arrest fueled a national furor over sexual abuse in the military.
lead_paragraph: Lt. Col. Jeffrey Krusinski, 42, who once led the branch’s sexual assault response team, was acquitted on charges that he had grabbed a woman outside a Virginia bar.
